<h3>DisABILITY</h3>
<hr>
<ul>
<li>ADA Americans with Disabilities Act -- <a href="http://www.sun.com/smli/projects/enabling-tech/additional.read.html">http://www.sun.com/smli/projects/enabling-tech/additional.read.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>ADA and Disability Information- links to ADA and disability-related resources -- <a href="http://www.public.iasta te.edu/~sbilling/ada.html">http://www.public.iasta te.edu/~sbilling/ada.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>ADA- the text of regulations and more -- <a href="http://www.gnn.com/gnn/wic/govt.25.html">http://www.gnn.com/gnn/wic/govt.25.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Americans with Disabilities Act gopher -- <a href="gopher://val-dor.cc.buffalo.edu:70/11/.legislation/">gopher://val-dor.cc.buffalo.edu:70/11/.legislation/</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Deaf and Hard of Hearing People, Directory of National Organizations of and for -- <a href="http://www.gallaudet.edu/~nicd/184.html">http://www.gallaudet.edu/~nicd/184.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Deaf Rights -- <a href="gopher://burrow.cl.msu.edu:70/11/msu/dept/deaf/general">gopher://burrow.cl.msu.edu:70/11/msu/dept/deaf/general</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Information and Program Guide re: Descriptive Video Service, a national service that makes television broadcast programs and movies on video accessible 
to blind and visually impaired people. Also may be contacted at <a href="mailto:DVS@wgbh.org">DVS@wgbh.org</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Directory of National Organizations of and for Deaf and Hard of Hearing People -- <a href="http://www.gallaudet.edu/~nicd/184.html">http://www.gallaudet.edu/~nicd/184.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Disability Info. at the Trace Center (TC specializes in rehabilitation engineering research) -- <a href="gopher://TRACE.wisc.edu:70">gopher://TRACE.wisc.edu:70</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Disability Information on the Web -- <a href="http://www.eskimo.com/~jlubin/disabled.html">http://www.eskimo.com/~jlubin/disabled.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Disability Legislation and Legal Issues -- <a href="gopher://sjumusic.stjohns.edu:70/1/-GOP/@uni:legal.menu">gopher://sjumusic.stjohns.edu:70/1/-GOP/@uni:legal.menu</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Disability resource list at Stanford University -- <a href="http ://akebono.stanford.edu/yahoo/Society_and_Culture/Disabilities/">http ://akebono.stanford.edu/yahoo/Society_and_Culture/Disabilities/</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Disability Resources at Emory U. Health Sciences Center Library -- <a href="http://www.cc.emory.edu/WHSCL/medweb.disabled.html">http://www.cc.emory.edu/WHSCL/medweb.disabled.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>EASI: Equal access to Software and Information (new website devoted to information technology and its access by persons with disabilities) -- 
<a href="http://www.rit.edu/~easi">http://www.rit.edu/~easi</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Eastern Paralyzed Veterans Associations -- <a href="http://www.epva.org">http://www.epva.org</a><img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Education Law -- <a href="http://access2.digex.net:80/~edlawinc/">http://access2.digex.net:80/~edlawinc/</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Evan Kemp Associates, Inc.:Disability Resources, Products, Services and Communication (includes free guide to consumer protection and a newsletter) -- 
<a href="http://disability.com/">http://disability.com/</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>The Integrated Network of Disability Information and Education - Info-route sur la d&eacute;ficience vers l'int&eacute;gration et l'&eacute;ducation -- <a href="http://indie.ca/">http://indie.ca/</a><img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>The Science, Engineering, and Math (SEM) Program. The SEM Program strives to increase the number of individuals with disabilities in SEM academic 
programs and professions -- <a href="http://www.asel.udel.edu/sem/">http://www.asel.udel.edu/sem/</a><img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Send mail to Duncan C. Kinder, Attorney at Law (ADA Law Specialist) -- <a href="mailto:DCKinder@aol.com">DCKinder@aol.com</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Self Help for Hard of Hearing People: Hearing Loss and the Hard of Hearing: Identifying, Understanding and Coping -- 
<a href="http://seamless.com/alexanderlaw/ftc/shhhh.html">http://seamless.com/alexanderlaw/ftc/shhhh.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Traumatic Brain Injury and the Law -- <a href="http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/txt/ability.html/talf/txt/trabrain.html">http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/txt/ability.html/talf/txt/trabrain.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Traumatic Brain Injury: Proving a Lifetime Disability -- <a href="http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/txt/trabrain.html">http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/txt/trabrain.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Understanding the Americans with Disability Act -- <a href="http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/disact.html">http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/disact.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
<li>Webmaster Disability Information: links to resources in the areas of &quot;General, Education, and Government; Healthcare and Medicine; University Based 
Disability Information; and Disability-Related Legal Resources&quot; -- <a href="http://disserv.stu.umn.edu/other.html">http://disserv.stu.umn.edu/other.html</a> <img src="../pixel.gif" align=top width=1 height=25></li>
