<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right5"><strong>5</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer c:</strong> The only advertisements over which the Food and Drug Administration has direct jurisdiction are 
those for prescription drugs. The Federal Trade Commission oversees advertising for other Food and Drug Administration 
regulated products. </p>
<p>TV sets are regulated under the radiological health provisions of the Food Drug &amp; Cosmetic Act. All televisions must comply 
with a performance standard that ensures their safety. This standard also applies to video display terminals used with computers. 
Over-the-counter and prescription drugs, as well as human biological products (such as vaccines and blood products), are 
regulated by the Food and Drug Administration. </p>
<p><a href="#5">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
