<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right6"><strong>6</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer a:</strong> Baby pacifiers are regulated by the Consumer Product Safety Commission unless they are 
marketed with health claims, in which case they are under the Food and Drug Administration's jurisdiction. </p>
<p>Food-contact articles, including baby bottle nipples, ceramic ware intended for food use, and coffee mugs, are regulated by the 
Food and Drug Administration. So are eye charts, which, as diagnostic products, are considered to be medical devices. </p>
<p><a href="#6">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right7"><strong>7</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer a:</strong> Illegal use of heroin is the responsibility of the Drug Enforcement Administration, the key federal 
agency that polices illicit, or &quot;street,&quot; drugs. (If heroin were being studied for medical uses, Food and Drug Administration would 
regulate it as an investigational drug.) </p>
<p>Barbiturates are subject to abuse and thus may, potentially, wind up on the &quot;street,&quot; bringing them under DEA's purview. 
However, barbiturates have legitimate medical uses, and the Food and Drug Administration is responsible for ensuring they are 
properly manufactured and labeled. The Food and Drug Administration regulates methadone as a drug, and methadone 
maintenance treatment programs are monitored under regulation promulgated by both the Food and Drug Administration and the 
National Institute on Drug Abuse (NIDA). Medicinal oxygen is regulated by the Food and Drug Administration as a drug. 
Animal drugs, including veterinary tetracycline, are regulated by Food and Drug Administration. </p>
<p><a href="#7">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
