</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right8"><strong>8</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer e:</strong> Hair dryers are regulated by the Consumer Product Safety Commission. </p>
<p>Kidney dialysis machines and tongue depressors, as different as they are in complexity, are both considered to be medical 
devices. The Food and Drug Administration regulates non-fluoridated toothpastes as cosmetics, and fluoridated toothpastes as 
drugs. </p>
<p><a href="#8">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
