</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right9"><strong>9</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer a:</strong> Labels on beer and other malt beverages, distilled spirits (liquors), and wines are regulated by the 
Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms under the Federal Alcohol Administration Act. </p>
<p>Ground coffee, coffee beans, rabbit meat, and canned tuna are all regulated by the Food and Drug Administration as foods. (The 
Federal Meat Inspection Act, which gives the U.S. Department of Agriculture authority over meat products, covers cattle, 
sheep, swine, goats, and horses. Other meat products, including game meats such as rabbit, are regulated by the Food and Drug 
Administration.) </p>
<p><a href="#9">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
