</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right12"><strong>12</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer a:</strong> A vaccine for horses is a veterinary biological product. The Food and Drug Administration does 
not have jurisdiction over veterinary biologics. The Virus, Serum, and Toxin Act gives this responsibility to the U. S.Department 
of Agriculture. </p>
<p>The Food Drug &amp; Cosmetic Act gives the Food and Drug Administration authority over pet foods and drugs, which would 
include veterinary penicillin, medicated feeds, and bird feed. The Public Health Service Act confers on the Food and Drug 
Administration the authority to regulate the interstate movement of psittacine birds (parrots, cockatoos, macaws, parakeets, and 
other birds in the psittacine family). These birds are potential carriers of psittacosis, a disease that can be transmitted to people. 
Psittacosis, which is also known as parrot fever, can range in severity from a mild respiratory infection to a protracted illness. </p>
<p><a href="#12">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
