<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
<a name="right13"><strong>13</strong></a><strong>. CORRECT! - Answer a:</strong> The safety of public drinking water (tap water) is protected by EPA, as decided in an agreement 
between that agency and the Food and Drug Administration. </p>
<p>The Food and Drug Administration has jurisdiction over bottled water, which is considered a food under the Food Drug &amp; 
Cosmetic Act. The remaining choices are also defined as foods. </p>
<p><a href="#13">Press here</a> to return to the quiz. </p>
<p><br>
<br>
